dlargest supplier of iron ore producing over Â million tonnes in calendar year  the companys major iron ore mines and development projects are located in australia south america canada india and guinea major subsidiaries held within rtit include hamersley iron majority interest in the pilbara iron mines and the iron ore company of canada the company also runs smelting facilities for the production of iron and steelâlimited in size in comparison to the massive amount of iron ore producedâat qitfer et titane in canada and hismelt in australia titanium dioxide is mined at three locations in canada south africa and madagascar and refined at qitfer et titanes canadian facilities major subsidiaries include richards bay minerals of south africa and qit madagascar minerals in  rio tinto produced Â million tonnes of titanium dioxide or approximately  of the estimated global production of Â million tonnes a media report in october  revealed that the corporation plans to establish a fully automated railroad system for the transportation of iron ore across the australian outback by  thereby replacing the groups train drivers the united kingdombased transport historian christian wolmar stated at the same time that the train drivers are most likely the highestpaid members of the occupation in the world at that time as part of an overall strategy to increase profit margins the group is spending us million on the project pilbara iron maintains the pilbara rail company to serve its western australia iron ore mines financial resultsedit rio tinto groups revenues and earnings have grown substantially in â with one of the largest increases attributable to the companys acquisition of alcan in  although operating margin is significantly impacted by the market prices of the various commodities it produces rio tinto has remained profitable over its recent history and consistently generated positive cash flows from operations earnings data in us millions               gross sales reve